class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kes1665702553734.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kes1665702553734.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kes1665702553734.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kes1665702553734\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"kes1665702553734__sort_list_240766\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Sort an associative list, an indexed list, or an indexed list of\n      sub-lists.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"kes1665702553734__topic_d77489e1_d77490e1_d77491e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kes1665702553734__p_d77492e1_d77493e1_d77494e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sort/list</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">List</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SortElement</var> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOptions</var>}  {<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SortElement</var>{<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOptions</var>}}<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kes1665702553734__p_d77495e1_d77496e1_d77497e1\">Syntax of <var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOptions</var>: {<var class=\"keyword varname\">Order</var>} {<var class=\"keyword varname\">Unique</var>} {<var class=\"keyword varname\">Type</var>}</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"kes1665702553734__section_w2293ab1b7b5_w2294ab1b7_w2295ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kes1665702553734__p_d77498e1_d77499e1_d77500e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">sort/list (vList, \"$idpart: descending numeric<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>$valuepart:a\")</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kes1665702553734__topic_d50977e1_d50978e1_d50979e1_d50980e1_d50981e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d526179e125\">Parameters</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20__entry__1\">Parameter</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20__entry__2\">Data Type</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20__entry__3\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">List</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20__entry__2\">String</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20__entry__3\">Uniface list to be sorted. The list can be\n\t\t\t\t an associative list of <var class=\"keyword varname\">Id=Value</var> pairs, such as a ValRep list or property list,\n\t\t\t\t an indexed list, or an indexed list of sub-lists. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SortElement</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20__entry__2\">String</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20__entry__3\">Element of an associative list, or a sub-list\n                        element, on which to sort:<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e83\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$idpart</span>—sort on the <var class=\"keyword varname\">IdPart</var> of an\n                              associative list</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e92\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$valuepart</span>—sort on the <var class=\"keyword varname\">ValuePart</var>\n                              of an associative list</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e101\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$string</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SublistItemId</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>—sort on the <var class=\"keyword varname\">IdPart</var> of an\n                              associative sub-list</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e119\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SublistItemNr</var>—sort on the sequence number of an\n                              indexed sub-list</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e126\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> For a multi-level sort, you can specify multiple\n                              <var class=\"keyword varname\">SortElement:SortOptions</var> parameters as a Uniface\n                           list or as a comma-separated list.</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOptions</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20__entry__2\">String</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__d6189e20__entry__3\">Sort options specifying the sort order,\n\t\t\t\t uniqueness, and NLS sorting rules. They can be defined in any order, separated by spaces. If a list\n\t\t\t\t is specified without sort options, the data is sorted in ascending order.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kes1665702553734__topic_d50987e1_d50988e1_d50989e1_d50990e1_d50991e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d526179e263\">Options</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Sort Options</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__1\">Sort Option</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\">Valid Values</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Order</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ascending</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">A</code>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">descending</code> | <span class=\"keyword option\">D</span>\n</p></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\">Sort order</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Unique</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">unique</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">U</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\">Keep only unique items; discard duplicates.\n                        <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eds1665702557855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eds1665702557855.html\" title=\"The following examples demonstrate how you can use the sort options to control sorting behavior.\">Using Sort Options</a>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"19\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Type</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\">Determines how sorting is performed by\n                     specifying the locale, case sensitivity, level, or data type. If not specified,\n                     the default is <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">nlslocale</span>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">nlslocale</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">NLS</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\">Sort as a string using the value of\n                        <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$nlssortorder</span>. If this is not set, the value of\n                        <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$nlslocale</span> is used. If this is not set, a binary sort is\n                     performed. <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jvl1665702552585.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jvl1665702552585.html\" title=\"You can sort data in ProcScript using several ProcScript statements and functions. The default sort order is determined by the data type of the data and the values of NLS settings.\">Sorting Based on Locale</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">CaseSensitive</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">CS</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">classic</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\">Sort as a case-sensitive string, ignoring\n\t\t\t\t locale-based sorting conventions.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">CaseInsensitive</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">CI</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\">Sort as a case-insensitive string, using\n\t\t\t\t the 1-to-1 character matching for Unicode uppercase and lowercase rules. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">level</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\">Sort data as level ID\n                     (<var class=\"keyword varname\">n.n.n</var>), so that <code class=\"ph codeph\">9.2</code> is sorted before\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">10.1</code>. <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eds1665702557855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eds1665702557855.html\" title=\"The following examples demonstrate how you can use the sort options to control sorting behavior.\">Using Sort Options</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2 kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"kes1665702553734__note_w2253ab1b3b1b3b9c15b1b1_w2254ab1b3b1b3b9c15b1_w2255ab1b3b1b3b9c15_w2256ab1b3b1b3b9_w2257ab1b3b1b3_w2258ab1b3b1_w2259ab1b3_w2260ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> When specifying the following sort\n      options, it is assumed the data is in a format that can be interpreted as the specified data\n      type. <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eds1665702557855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eds1665702557855.html#eds1665702557855__section_p55_wjx_tcc\">Example: Sorting Using Data Type</a>.</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">Numeric</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\"> Sort data as Numeric</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">Float</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\"> Sort data as Float</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">Boolean</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\"> Sort data as Boolean</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">Date</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\"> Sort data as Date</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">Time</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\"> Sort data as Time</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2 kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"kes1665702553734__note_w2261ab1b3b1b3b9c27b1b1_w2262ab1b3b1b3b9c27b1_w2263ab1b3b1b3b9c27_w2264ab1b3b1b3b9_w2265ab1b3b1b3_w2266ab1b3b1_w2267ab1b3_w2268ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> When specifying the following sort options, Uniface converts the data to the specified data type before sorting:</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$number</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\"> Sort Data as\n                        <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$number</span><code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$float</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\"> Sort Data as\n                        <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$float</span><code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$boolean</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\"> Sort Data as\n                        <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$boolean</span><code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$date</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\"> Sort Data as\n                        <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$date</span><code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$time</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\"> Sort Data as\n                        <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$clock</span><code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$datim</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\"> Sort Data as\n                        <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$datim</span><code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$string</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7451e1_d7452e1_d7453e1__entry__3\"> Sort Data as\n                        <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$string</span><code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kes1665702553734__topic_d50997e1_d50998e1_d50999e1_d51000e1_d51001e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d526179e688\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7478e1_d7479e1_d7480e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7478e1_d7479e1_d7480e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7478e1_d7479e1_d7480e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7478e1_d7479e1_d7480e1__entry__1\">\n &lt;0\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7478e1_d7479e1_d7480e1__entry__2\">\n An error occurred. <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> contains the exact error.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7478e1_d7479e1_d7480e1__entry__1\">\n 0\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7478e1_d7479e1_d7480e1__entry__2\">\n Success\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7478e1_d7479e1_d7480e1__entry__1\">\n &gt;=0\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7478e1_d7479e1_d7480e1__entry__2\">\n Number of items remaining in <var class=\"keyword varname\">List</var>.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 4. </span><span class=\"title\">Sort List Errors Commonly Returned in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span></span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__1\"> Value </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__2\"> Error constant </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__3\"> Meaning </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"6\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-1112</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"6\">UPROCERR_OPTION</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__3\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOption</var>: Ascending\n                     assumed: When an option starts with an \"A\" and is not \"A\" / \"ASC\" /\n                     \"ASCENDING\".</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__3\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOption</var>: Descending\n                     assumed: When an option starts with an \"D\" and is not \"D\" / \"DESC\" /\n                     \"DESCENDING\".</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__3\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOption</var>: Unique assumed:\n                     When an option starts with an \"U\" and is not \"U\" / \"UNI\" / \"UNIQUE\".</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__3\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOption</var>: Invalid option:\n                     When an option can't be recognized.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__3\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOption</var>: Duplicate order: When an Ascending is defined over\n\t\t\t\t a Descending v.v.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__3\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOption</var>: Duplicate type: When a <var class=\"keyword varname\">DataType</var>\n\t\t\t\t or $<var class=\"keyword varname\">Typing</var> is defined twice.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-1101</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__2\">UPROCERR_FIELD</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__3\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOption</var>: Field does not\n                     exist For sort \"entity\" when a fieldname is wrong or excluded. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-1129</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"2\">UPROCERR_ITEM</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__3\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOption</var>:\n                        <var class=\"keyword varname\">SubItemId</var> does not exist.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kes1665702553734__table_d7481e1_d7482e1_d7483e1__entry__3\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOption</var>:\n                        <var class=\"keyword varname\">SubItemNr</var> does not exist. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kes1665702553734__topic_d51002e1_d51003e1_d51004e1_d51005e1_d51006e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d526179e904\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kes1665702553734__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kes1665702553734__topic_d51007e1_d51008e1_d51009e1_d51010e1_d51011e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d526179e913\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kes1665702553734__p_d77528e1_d77529e1_d77530e1\">By default, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sort/list</span> sorts on the value part of a list item, in ascending order. Sorting is based on the first 8K of the item data.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kes1665702553734__p_d77531e1_d77532e1_d77533e1\">The values of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$nlssortorder</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$nlslocale</span> determine whether locale-based sorting rules are applied. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jvl1665702552585.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jvl1665702552585.html\" title=\"You can sort data in ProcScript using several ProcScript statements and functions. The default sort order is determined by the data type of the data and the values of NLS settings.\">Sorting Based on Locale</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kes1665702553734__p_d77534e1_d77535e1_d77536e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vkk1665702553651.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vkk1665702553651.html\" title=\"Uniface provides ProcScript instructions for sorting entity occurrences in hitlists and lists created in ProcScript. It is possible to perform multi-level sorting, enabling you to sort by several fields, each with its own sort criteria.\">Sorting Data in ProcScript</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kes1665702553734__section_xms_mcs_5bc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d526179e951\">Example: Sorting Lists by ID and by Value</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Given the following list:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"kes1665702553734__pre_vcw_ncs_5bc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vColors = \"\"\nputitem/id vColors \"0\", \"BLUE\"\nputitem/id vColors \"1\", \"RED\"\nputitem/id vColors \"2\", \"GREEN\"\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">You can sort the list by the ID part:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"kes1665702553734__pre_wcw_ncs_5bc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">sort/list (vColors, \"$idpart: descending numeric\")\n\n;Result: vColors = \"2=GREEN<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>1=RED<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>0=BLUE\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">or by the value part (the default):</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"kes1665702553734__pre_xcw_ncs_5bc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">sort/list (vColors, \"ascending\")\n\n;Result: vColors = \"0=BLUE<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>2=GREEN<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>1=RED\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kes1665702553734__section_nqn_bcs_5bc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d526179e988\">Example: Sorting Lists in Fields</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">In the following example, STATE is a drop-down list field. The ValRep for\n            the field STATE contains fifty possibilities, in which the value is the state\n            abbreviation and the representation is the state name: <code class=\"ph codeph\">ak=Alaska<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>al=Alabama<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>ar=Arkansas<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>az=Arizona</code> and so on.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The field STATE, however, has only a single value so it is not possible\n            to sort on STATE, so the ValRep list must be copied into a variable before sorting can\n            be effective.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"kes1665702553734__pre_yw1_ccs_5bc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger getFocus; on Entity\nvStates = $valrep(STATE)\nsort/list vStates,\"A\" \n; vStates is now \"al=Alabama<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>ak=Alaska<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>az=Arizona<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>ar=Arkansas\" ...\n$valrep(STATE) = vStates\nend ; getFocus</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cip1665702554022.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>List Handling in ProcScript</a><p>Uniface provides ProcScript instructions that enable you to build lists, retrieve items from lists, and sort lists based on various criteria.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vkk1665702553651.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Sorting Data in ProcScript</a><p>Uniface provides ProcScript instructions for sorting entity occurrences in hitlists and lists created in ProcScript. It is possible to perform multi-level sorting, enabling you to sort by several fields, each with its own sort criteria.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qwg1665702557778.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Sorting Lists and Sublists</a><p>The ProcScript commands sort/list, $sortlist, and $sortlistid enable you to sort all kinds of lists, including indexed lists (flat lists), associative lists (such as property lists and ValRep lists), and nested lists (such as those used in tree widgets).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jvl1665702552585.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Sorting Based on Locale</a><p>You can sort data in ProcScript using several ProcScript statements and functions. The default sort order is determined by the data type of the data and the values of NLS settings.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jei1665702553041.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>sort</a><p>Sort the occurrences in the hitlist for the specified entity.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/raa1718953684079.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$sortlist</a><p>Sort an associative list, an indexed list, or an indexed list of sublists.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wqe1719856383580.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$sortlistid</a><p>Sort an associative list in which the value part of each list item is an indexed list.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529182\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529182\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "sort/list Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Sort an associative list, an indexed list, or an indexed list of sub-lists. sort/list List , \" SortElement { : SortOptions } { ; SortElement { : SortOptions }} \" Syntax of SortOptions : { Order } { Unique } { Type } Example: sort/list (vList, \"$idpart: descending numeric ; $valuepart:a\") Parameters Table 1. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description List String Uniface list to be sorted. The list can be an associative list of Id=Value pairs, such as a ValRep list or property list, an indexed list, or an indexed list of sub-lists. SortElement String Element of an associative list, or a sub-list element, on which to sort: $idpart —sort on the IdPart of an associative list $valuepart —sort on the ValuePart of an associative list $string ( SublistItemId ) —sort on the IdPart of an associative sub-list SublistItemNr —sort on the sequence number of an indexed sub-list Note: For a multi-level sort, you can specify multiple SortElement:SortOptions parameters as a Uniface list or as a comma-separated list. SortOptions String Sort options specifying the sort order, uniqueness, and NLS sorting rules. They can be defined in any order, separated by spaces. If a list is specified without sort options, the data is sorted in ascending order. Options Table 2. Sort Options Sort Option Valid Values Meaning Order ascending | A descending | D Sort order Unique unique | U Keep only unique items; discard duplicates. Using Sort Options . Type Determines how sorting is performed by specifying the locale, case sensitivity, level, or data type. If not specified, the default is nlslocale . nlslocale | NLS Sort as a string using the value of $nlssortorder . If this is not set, the value of $nlslocale is used. If this is not set, a binary sort is performed. Sorting Based on Locale . CaseSensitive | CS | classic Sort as a case-sensitive string, ignoring locale-based sorting conventions. CaseInsensitive | CI Sort as a case-insensitive string, using the 1-to-1 character matching for Unicode uppercase and lowercase rules. level Sort data as level ID ( n.n.n ), so that 9.2 is sorted before 10.1 . Using Sort Options . Note: When specifying the following sort options, it is assumed the data is in a format that can be interpreted as the specified data type. Example: Sorting Using Data Type . Numeric Sort data as Numeric Float Sort data as Float Boolean Sort data as Boolean Date Sort data as Date Time Sort data as Time Note: When specifying the following sort options, Uniface converts the data to the specified data type before sorting: $number Sort Data as $number ( String ) $float Sort Data as $float ( String ) $boolean Sort Data as $boolean ( String ) $date Sort Data as $date ( String ) $time Sort Data as $clock ( String ) $datim Sort Data as $datim ( String ) $string Sort Data as $string ( String ) Return Values Table 3. Values returned in $status Value Meaning <0 An error occurred. $procerror contains the exact error. 0 Success >=0 Number of items remaining in List . Table 4. Sort List Errors Commonly Returned in $procerror Value Error constant Meaning -1112 UPROCERR_OPTION SortOption : Ascending assumed: When an option starts with an \"A\" and is not \"A\" / \"ASC\" / \"ASCENDING\". SortOption : Descending assumed: When an option starts with an \"D\" and is not \"D\" / \"DESC\" / \"DESCENDING\". SortOption : Unique assumed: When an option starts with an \"U\" and is not \"U\" / \"UNI\" / \"UNIQUE\". SortOption : Invalid option: When an option can't be recognized. SortOption : Duplicate order: When an Ascending is defined over a Descending v.v. SortOption : Duplicate type: When a DataType or $ Typing is defined twice. -1101 UPROCERR_FIELD SortOption : Field does not exist For sort \"entity\" when a fieldname is wrong or excluded. -1129 UPROCERR_ITEM SortOption : SubItemId does not exist. SortOption : SubItemNr does not exist. Use Allowed in all component types. Description By default, sort/list sorts on the value part of a list item, in ascending order. Sorting is based on the first 8K of the item data. The values of $nlssortorder and $nlslocale determine whether locale-based sorting rules are applied. For more information, see Sorting Based on Locale . For more information, see Sorting Data in ProcScript . Example: Sorting Lists by ID and by Value Given the following list: vColors = \"\" putitem/id vColors \"0\", \"BLUE\" putitem/id vColors \"1\", \"RED\" putitem/id vColors \"2\", \"GREEN\" Copy You can sort the list by the ID part: sort/list (vColors, \"$idpart: descending numeric\") ;Result: vColors = \"2=GREEN ; 1=RED ; 0=BLUE\" Copy or by the value part (the default): sort/list (vColors, \"ascending\") ;Result: vColors = \"0=BLUE ; 2=GREEN ; 1=RED\" Copy Example: Sorting Lists in Fields In the following example, STATE is a drop-down list field. The ValRep for the field STATE contains fifty possibilities, in which the value is the state abbreviation and the representation is the state name: ak=Alaska ; al=Alabama ; ar=Arkansas ; az=Arizona and so on. The field STATE, however, has only a single value so it is not possible to sort on STATE, so the ValRep list must be copied into a variable before sorting can be effective. trigger getFocus; on Entity vStates = $valrep(STATE) sort/list vStates,\"A\" ; vStates is now \"al=Alabama ; ak=Alaska ; az=Arizona ; ar=Arkansas\" ... $valrep(STATE) = vStates end ; getFocus Copy Related Links List Handling in ProcScript Uniface provides ProcScript instructions that enable you to build lists, retrieve items from lists, and sort lists based on various criteria. Sorting Data in ProcScript Uniface provides ProcScript instructions for sorting entity occurrences in hitlists and lists created in ProcScript. It is possible to perform multi-level sorting, enabling you to sort by several fields, each with its own sort criteria. Sorting Lists and Sublists The ProcScript commands sort/list, $sortlist, and $sortlistid enable you to sort all kinds of lists, including indexed lists (flat lists), associative lists (such as property lists and ValRep lists), and nested lists (such as those used in tree widgets). Sorting Based on Locale You can sort data in ProcScript using several ProcScript statements and functions. The default sort order is determined by the data type of the data and the values of NLS settings. sort Sort the occurrences in the hitlist for the specified entity. $sortlist Sort an associative list, an indexed list, or an indexed list of sublists. $sortlistid Sort an associative list in which the value part of each list item is an indexed list. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}